HEADWORD: Abderian
<hw>Ab*de"ri*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Abdera</ets>, a town in Thrace, of which place Democritus, the
Laughing Philosopher, was a native.]</ety> <def>Given to laughter;
inclined to foolish or incessant merriment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abderite</ent>⟦br⟧
